data.description: OWN A PIECE OF ERIE HISTORY! BUILT AROUND 1830, THIS 3440 SQUARE FOOT HOME IS AFFECTIONATELY REFERRED TO AS THE WALLACE-KNOX HOUSE, PAYING TRIBUTE TO ITS FIRST OWNERS. THE FOUR BEDROOM BRICK CLASSIC FEATURES SPACIOUS ROOMS, ORIGINAL TULIP POPLAR (HARDWOOD) FLOORS, AND BEAUTIFUL BUILT-INS THROUGHOUT. FIREPLACES IN DINING & FAMILY ROOMS ARE WOOD BURNING, AND THE LIVING ROOM FIREPLACE IS GAS. A SWEEPING STAIRCASE LEADS FROM THE FOYER TO THE SECOND FLOOR. THE LANDSCAPED YARD IS FRAMED BY LARGE TREES AND WROUGHT IRON FENCING, ENSURING PRIVACY AND A LOVELY SPACE FOR ENTERTAINING. A BRICK PATIO AND TWO STORY SCREENED-IN PORCH OFFER ADDITIONAL SPACE TO ENJOY THE QUIET NEIGHBORHOOD. SHOWINGS START FRIDAY AFTER 3.00 PM
